      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422494_1821_10_09_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <hi rend="underline">Very private</hi>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1821-10-09"/>Oct<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 9<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1821. </dateline>
               <salute>
                  Sir<lb/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I take the liberty of enclosing to you<lb/>
               copies of letters from <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SidmH1">Lord Sidmouth</persName>
               <lb/>
               to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FostJ2">Lord Oriel</persName> - dated 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. Sept<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. - <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName>
               <lb/>
               <add>also from</add>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TalbJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Talbot</persName> to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauM1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Beaufort</persName> same date<lb/>
               <add>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName>
               </add> And another from <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TalbJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Talbot</persName> â€” Oct 2 â€”<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>By <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TalbJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Talbots</persName> of the 24<hi rend="superscript">h</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauM1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. B.</persName>
               <lb/>
               is informed that her pension which<lb/>
               was 30 <hi rend="superscript">Â£</hi> is increased to 50 <hi rend="superscript">Â£</hi> per Annum.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I conceive therefore that 50 <hi rend="superscript">Â£</hi> per Annum<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">was</hi>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauM1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Beaufort</persName>'s actual pension from<lb/>
               Government here, when <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SidmH1">Lord Sidmouth</persName>
               <lb/>
               "transmitted his Majesty's commands<lb/>
               " <del>that</del> to the Irish Government to make<lb/>
               "an addition of 50 <hi rend="superscript">Â£</hi> per Ann<hi rend="superscript">m</hi>. to her<lb/>
               "<hi rend="underline">present</hi>
               <hi rend="underline">pension</hi>" -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>She has been informed however<lb/>
               in <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TalbJ1">Mr. Talbots</persName> letter of Oct 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. that her<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422494_1821_10_09_page02.jpg"/>
               
               pension is only 80 <hi rend="superscript">Â£</hi> per Annum --<lb/>
               â€” I think this is a mistake â€” If it be<lb/>
               not will you have the goodness to<lb/>
               explain it to me.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I know Sir how benevolently<lb/>
               you have been interested in this <choice>
                  <orig>busi<lb/>
                  ness</orig>
                  <reg>business</reg>
               </choice> &amp; I make no apology for asking<lb/>
               this question.<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I have the honor to be<lb/>
               with great respect<lb/>
               your most Obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
